In a statement, the party said she passed away on Monday morning in Kwaphindangene in KwaZulu-Natal. JOHANNESBURG - The Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) has confirmed Irene Buthelezi, the wife of Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, has died after a long illness.In a statement, the party said she passed away on Monday morning in Kwaphindangene, in KwaZulu-Natal. The Buthelezi family has asked for privacy, as they arrange her funeral. The family has thanked friends and supporters for their condolences and prayers. The couple had been married for 67 years. Their son Prince Ntuthukoyezwe Zuzifa said: “I think to have known somebody for that long, they become part of your DNA so it’s very difficult for our father, especially because both of them as parents have lost five siblings, one after the other.” The Desmond and Leah Tutu Foundation says it's saddened to learn of the passing of Princess Irene. The foundation has joined the outpouring of condolences for her family. My deepest condolences to Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi and his family for the loss of his wife, Irene. May her soul Rest In Peace.  Statement by the Buthelezi Family on the passing of Princess Irene Audrey Thandekile Buthelezi (nee Mzila) the beloved wife of Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi. pic.twitter.com/xmpOaZ0IEs  EFF Sends Condolences To The Buthelezis On The Passing Of Princess Irene Audrey Thandekile Buthelezi pic.twitter.com/WoiFoerOQG  May Princess Irene Audrey Thandekile Buthelezi Rest In Peace condolences to the Buthelezi family Sokwalisa @IFPinParliament @MkhulekoHlengwa pic.twitter.com/HA6uBTAXDO 